fields.descriptive_line: Large Dolls' house, home-made,  English, ca 1934
fields.physical_description: The house has 3 stories (4 if you count the base), there is a central building with a wing on its left side.  The house is constructed of wood and is covered in printed paper to represent either bricks or tiles.  The architectural details around the doors, windows and roof are painted in white.  The house sits on a large purpose built plinth/base unit, the top of the base is decorated as a garden including paths and green areas for grass.  The is a ramp and gateway on the right side of the building.  The base has casters.  The rooms are accessed at the back with removable panels.  The house comes with a collection of furniture.
fields.dimensions: Height: 117 cm, Width: 140.5 cm, Depth: 74.5 cm
fields.title: The Turing House
fields.materials_techniques: maily wood and paper.  Furniture is mixed material.
